<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Familiar2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Familiar,</orth> subst. 1) a particular friend: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 2, 10</bibl>.<lb />2) a demon or attendant spirit: <cit><quote>love is a f</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.177" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 177</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>her old f. is asleep,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 122</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he has a f. under his tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.7.114" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 7, 114</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Familiar</emph> adj. def. 1).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>